2.0     MAJOR CHANGES IN COBOL V6


     2.1        DATA BASE CAPABILITY


     2.1.1      NEW FEATURES

     PROCEDURE DIVISION DML VERBS HAVE BEEN INCORPORATED INTO THE
     COBOL  COMPILER.   THESE  VERBS  ALLOW THE USER TO INTERFACE
     WITH THE DECSYSTEM-10 DATA BASE FACILITIES (DBMS-10) WITHOUT
     REQUIRING  THE USE OF A PRE-PROCESSOR.  FOR MORE INFORMATION
     SEE THE DBMS PROGRAMMER'S PROCEDURES  MANUAL  AND  THE  DBMS
     DATA BASE ADMINISTRATOR'S PROCEDURES MANUAL.

     NEW FEATURES IN COBOL VERSION 6 FOR THIS PURPOSE ARE:


          SCHEMA SECTION

                  THE DATA DIVISION SECTION IN  A  COBOL  PROGRAM
                  WHERE  THE  DATA  BASE SUB-SCHEMA IS "INVOKED".
                  THE  SCHEMA  SECTION  MUST  FOLLOW  IMMEDIATELY
                  AFTER  THE  DATA DIVISION HEADER, AND THERE MAY
                  ONLY BE ONE SCHEMA SECTION IN A PROGRAM.


          INVOKE

                  THE DATA DIVISION VERB USED TO  ESTABLISH  DATA
                  BASE  CAPABILITY  WITHIN  A  COBOL PROGRAM.  IT
                  SERVES THE PURPOSE  OF  ALLOCATING  THE  SYSTEM
                  COMMUNICATIONS LOCATIONS (SCL) AND DEFINING THE
                  RECORDS SPECIFIED IN THE SUB-SCHEMA.


          ACCESS

                  SAME AS INVOKE EXCEPT IS  FOR  SHARING  A  DATA
                  BASE  WITH  A  PROGRAM-UNIT  WHICH  HAS ALREADY
                  INVOKED IT.   CONCEPTUALLY  PLACES  RECORDS  IN
                  LINKAGE  SECTION  RATHER  THAN  WORKING-STORAGE
                  SECTION.


          CLOSE

                  A PROCEDURE DIVISION VERB  USED  TO  RELINQUISH
                  CONTROL  OVER THE SPECIFIED AREAS AND MAKE THEM
                  AVAILABLE  TO  OTHER  RUN-UNITS  WHICH  MAY  BE
                  DELAYED WAITING FOR THEM.


          DELETE
COBOL V6A(332) DOCUMENTATION                               Page 3


                  A  PROCEDURE  DIVISION  VERB  WHICH  MAKES  THE
                  OBJECT    RECORD    UNAVAILABLE   FOR   FURTHER
                  PROCESSING.


          FIND

                  A PROCEDURE DIVISION VERB WHICH  ESTABLISHES  A
                  PARTICULAR  RECORD  OCCURRENCE AS THE "CURRENT"
                  ONE.


          GET

                  A PROCEDURE DIVISION VERB USED TO TRANSFER  THE
                  CONTENTS  OF  THE  SPECIFIED  DATA  ITEM OF THE
                  OBJECT RECORD OCCURRENCE INTO THE USER  WORKING
                  AREA.


          INSERT

                  A VERB WHICH INCORPORATES  A  SPECIFIED  RECORD
                  OCCURRENCE  INTO  A NAMED SET, ACCORDING TO THE
                  SET MEMBERSHIP RESTRICTIONS WHICH WERE  DEFINED
                  IN THE DATA DEFINITION FILE.


          MODIFY

                  THE VERB USED TO REPLACE THE VALUES OF ALL,  OR
                  OF  SPECIFIC  DATA  ITEMS  OF THE OBJECT RECORD
                  OCCURRENCE IN THE DATABASE,  WITH  VALUES  FROM
                  THE USER WORKING AREA.


          OPEN

                  THIS VERB INITIALIZES AN  AREA  FOR  PROCESSING
                  AND SPECIFIES ITS USAGE MODE.


          REMOVE

                  THIS VERB CANCELS THE MEMBERSHIP OF THE  OBJECT
                  RECORD IN THE SPECIFIED SETS.


          STORE

                  THIS PROCEDURE DIVISION VERB ACQUIRES SPACE AND
                  A  DATABASE-KEY  FOR A NEW RECORD OCCURRENCE IN
                  THE DATABASE.
COBOL V6A(332) DOCUMENTATION                               Page 4


          USE IF ERROR-STATUS...

                  A PROCEDURE DIVISION  CLAUSE  USED  TO  SPECIFY
                  PROCEDURES   TO   BE  EXECUTED  WHEN  SPECIFIED
                  ERROR-STATUS CONDITIONS OCCUR.



     2.1.2      CONVERSION FROM PRE-PROCESSOR FORMAT

     ALL  COBOL  SOURCE  PROGRAMS  CAN  BE  CONVERTED  FROM   THE
     PRE-PROCESSOR  FORMAT  TO  THE STANDARD FORMAT QUITE EASILY.
     THE FOLLOWING MODIFICATIONS ARE THE ONLY ONES NECESSARY:


          1 )  INSERT "SCHEMA SECTION" IMMEDIATELY AFTER THE FILE
          SECTION,  IF  PRESENT, AND THE DATA DIVISION HEADING IF
          NOT.


          2 )  MOVE   THE    "INVOKE"    STATEMENT    FROM    THE
          WORKING-STORAGE SECTION TO THE SCHEMA SECTION.


     USERS SHOULD  BE  AWARE  THAT  ANY  ERRORS  IN  AN  "INVOKE"
     STATEMENT  IMPLY  THAT  ALL  DATA DEFINITIONS IN THE INVOKED
     SUB-SCHEMA WILL NOT BE CREATED BY THE COMPILER.   THEREFORE,
     ANY  SUCH  ERROR  WILL  MOST  LIKELY  PRODUCE NUMEROUS OTHER
     ERRORS LATER IN THE PROCEDURE DIVISION.



     2.1.3      RESTRICTIONS

     IN THE PROCEDURE DIVISION STATEMENT,  "OPEN  AREA  <AREA-1>,
     <AREA-2>,..."  ,  THERE  IS A MAXIMUM OF TEN (10) AREA-NAMES
     ALLOWED IN ONE STATEMENT.  IF MORE THAN TEN AREAS ARE TO  BE
     OPENED  AT ONCE, THEN MORE THAN ONE "OPEN" COMMAND WILL HAVE
     TO BE ISSUED.
