     2.2        COMMUNICATIONS CAPABILITY


     COBOL V6  INCLUDES  THE  FACILITIES  TO  ALLOW  PROGRAMS  TO
     ACCESS,  PROCESS,  AND  CREATE MESSAGES OR PORTIONS THEREOF.
     THESE MESSAGES ARE USED  IN  CONJUNCTION  WITH  THE  MESSAGE
     CONTROL SYSTEM (MCS-10) TO COMMUNICATE WITH LOCAL AND REMOTE
     COMMUNICATION DEVICES.

     THESE FACILITIES  INCLUDE  SEVERAL  NEW  PROCEDURE  DIVISION
     VERBS AND ONE NEW DATA DIVISION STRUCTURE:



          COMMUNICATION SECTION

                  THE COMMUNICATION SECTION IS USED IN  THE  DATA
                  DIVISION  AND  HAS  THE  FUNCTION  OF LOGICALLY
                  GROUPING TOGETHER  ALL  INFORMATION  CONCERNING
                  THE STRUCTURE OF THE MESSAGE QUEUES.


          COMMUNICATION DESCRIPTION (CD)

                  THE CD IS A DATA STRUCTURE WHICH SPECIFIES  THE
                  INTERFACE  AREA  BETWEEN  MCS-10  AND  A  COBOL
                  PROGRAM.    IT   MAY   APPEAR   ONLY   IN   THE
                  COMMUNICATION SECTION OF THE DATA DIVISION.


          ACCEPT COUNT

                  A PROCEDURE DIVISION VERB  WHICH  PERFORMS  THE
                  FUNCTION  OF STORING, IN A SPECIFIED DATA ITEM,
                  THE NUMBER OF ENTRIES IN A  PARTICULAR  MESSAGE
                  QUEUE.


          DISABLE

                  A VERB WHICH NOTIFIES MCS-10  TO  INHIBIT  DATA
                  TRANSFER  BETWEEN  THE SPECIFIED MESSAGE QUEUES
                  AND  A   PARTICULAR   SOURCE   OR   DESTINATION
                  TERMINAL.


          ENABLE

                  A VERB WHICH  NOTIFIES  MCS-10  TO  ALLOW  DATA
                  TRANSFER  BETWEEN  THE SPECIFIED MESSAGE QUEUES
                  AND  A   PARTICULAR   SOURCE   OR   DESTINATION
                  TERMINAL.


          IF MESSAGE ...
COBOL V6A(332) DOCUMENTATION                               Page 6


                  A PROCEDURE DIVISION STATEMENT WHICH TESTS  THE
                  STATUS  OF  THE SPECIFIED QUEUES.  IF THE QUEUE
                  IS NON-EMPTY, THEN THE STATEMENTS FOLLOWING THE
                  "IF    MESSAGE"    STATEMENT    ARE   EXECUTED.
                  OTHERWISE, CONTROL PASSES TO THE  NEXT  PROGRAM
                  SENTENCE.


          RECEIVE

                  A VERB  WHICH  MAKES  AVAILABLE  TO  THE  COBOL
                  PROGRAM   A  MESSAGE,  MESSAGE  SEGMENT,  OR  A
                  PORTION OF A MESSAGE OR SEGMENT, AND  PERTINENT
                  INFORMATION  ABOUT  THAT  DATA  FROM  A MESSAGE
                  QUEUE.  THE "RECEIVE" STATEMENT ALSO ALLOWS FOR
                  A  SPECIFIC IMPERATIVE STATEMENT TO BE EXECUTED
                  WHEN NO DATA IS AVAILABLE.


          SEND

                  A  VERB  WHICH  CAUSES  A  MESSAGE,  A  MESSAGE
                  SEGMENT,  OR  A PORTION OF A MESSAGE OR SEGMENT
                  TO BE RELEASED TO ONE  OR  MORE  OUTPUT  QUEUES
                  MAINTAINED BY MCS-10.
