     2.3        TEXT EDITING FACILITIES

     TWO OTHER VERBS, STRING AND UNSTRING,  HAVE  BEEN  ADDED  TO
     COBOL  V6.   THESE VERBS CONFORM TO THE ANSI-73 STANDARD AND
     PROVIDE FAIRLY  POWERFUL  STRING  MANIPULATION  CAPABILITIES
     WHICH  CAN  BE USED WITH OR WITHOUT MCS-10.  THESE VERBS ARE
     STANDARD IN ALL COBOL V6 RELEASE TAPES.



          STRING

                  THE STRING STATEMENT PROVIDES CONCATENATION  OF
                  THE PARTIAL OR COMPLETE CONTENTS OF TWO OR MORE
                  DATA  ITEMS  INTO  A  SINGLE  DATA  ITEM.   THE
                  CONTENTS  OF  EACH  SOURCE  DATA  ITEM  MAY  BE
                  DELIMITED EITHER BY A LITERAL, BY THE  SIZE  OF
                  THE  ITEM ITSELF, OR BY THE CONTENTS OF ANOTHER
                  DATA ITEM.  ALSO, THE STRING STATEMENT HAS  THE
                  FACILITY  FOR  PASSING  CONTROL  TO A SPECIFIED
                  IMPERATIVE STATEMENT ON THE CONDITION  OF  DATA
                  OVERFLOW.


          UNSTRING

                  THE UNSTRING STATEMENT CAUSES  CONTIGUOUS  DATA
                  IN  A  SOURCE  FIELD TO BE SEPARATED AND PLACED
                  INTO   MULTIPLE   DESTINATION   FIELDS.    THIS
                  STATEMENT  ALSO PROVIDES FACILITIES WHICH ALLOW
                  THE USER TO  ACCESS  THE  DELIMITING  CHARACTER
                  STRING  AND  TEXT  LENGTH  FOR EACH DESTINATION
                  DATA ITEM, THE COUNT OF DESTINATION ITEMS ACTED
                  UPON,  AND THE CHARACTER POSITION OF THE SOURCE
                  ITEM AT WHICH  THE  UNSTRING  OPERATION  IS  TO
                  BEGIN.
