     2.4        MINOR ENHANCEMENTS


     2.4.1      THE ASCII  CHARACTER  LEFT  BRACKET  "["  IS  NOW
     ASSIGNED  THE  NUMERIC VALUE "+0".  ALSO, THE CHARACTERS "!"
     AND "]" HAVE BEEN INCLUDED AS OVERPUNCH CHARACTERS WITH  THE
     VALUE "-0".

     2.4.2      PRELIMINARY OVERLAY FACILITY


     A PRELIMINARY LINK-10 OVERLAY FEATURE HAS BEEN  INCLUDED  IN
     COBOL  V6A.   FOR DOCUMENTATION SEE CHAPTER 5 OF THE LINK-10
     MANUAL IN SOFTWARE NOTEBOOK NUMBER 5.  THIS TYPE OF  OVERLAY
     IS SUBJECT TO THE FOLLOWING RESTRICTIONS:

          1.  NO IO IS PERMITTED IN AN OVERLAY SUBROUTINE.

          2.  IF AN ATTEMPT IS MADE BY LIBOL  TO  EXPAND  THE  IO
          BUFFER  AREA  INTO  THE  OVERLAY  AREA THE PROGRAM WILL
          TERMINATE WITH AN ERROR MESSAGE.  MOST BUFFER SPACE  IS
          ALLOCATED  AT RESET TIME.  ONLY SORT AND SOMETIMES ISAM
          FILES, WHEN ENOUGH WRITES ARE PERFORMED TO CREATE A NEW
          INDEX  LEVEL,  MAY REQUEST SPACE DYNAMICALLY.  THE USER
          MUST  ALLOCATE  SUFFICIENT  CORE  SPACE,  VIA  THE  THE
          LINK-10  /SPACE SWITCH, TO ACCOMMODATE THE PROGRAM'S IO
          BUFFERS AND ANY SORT IO BUFFERS AT LOAD TIME.

          3.  IF A CALL FOR AN OVERLAY  CAUSES  THE  END  OF  THE
          OVERLAY  AREA  TO EXTEND INTO THE SORT CORE BUFFER AREA
          THE PROGRAM WILL TERMINATE WITH AN ERROR MESSAGE.  NOTE
          -  THE  SORT CORE BUFFER AREA IS RELEASED AT THE END OF
          THE SORT.

     TO AVOID ANY CORE CONFLICTS THE USER MAY CHOOSE TO:

     1.  NOT WRITE INTO AN ISAM FILE AND

     2.  NOT CALL, WHILE A SORT  IS  IN  PROGRESS,  A  SUBROUTINE
     WHICH IS NOT IN THE ROOT SEGMENT.
