3.0     EXTERNAL CHANGES AND OPTIONS



     3.1        FEATURE TEST SWITCHES


     TWO NEW FEATURE TEST SWITCHES HAVE BEEN ADDED:   "DBMS"  AND
     "MCS".   IF  EITHER  OF THESE IS SET TO 1 IN COBASM.MAC, THE
     CORRESPONDING FACILITIES WILL BE ASSEMBLED INTO COBOL  V6  .
     HOWEVER, BOTH OF THESE FACILITIES REQUIRE THEIR OWN RUN-TIME
     SUPPORT MODULE WHICH IS SUPPLIED AS A SEPARATE PRODUCT.

     THE STRING AND UNSTRING VERBS ARE CONTROLLED BY  THE  SWITCH
     "STRING".  THIS SHOULD ALWAYS BE ON;  OTHERWISE, THE RESULTS
     OF THE ASSEMBLY MAY BE UNPREDICTABLE.  THE DEFAULT VALUE FOR
     THIS FEATURE TEST SWITCH IS ALWAYS "ON".



     3.2        NEW MODULES


     THERE ARE FOUR NEW MODULES IN THE COBOL COMPILER FOR VERSION
     6.   TWO  OF  THESE  MODULES ARE CONCERNED WITH DBMS-10, ONE
     WITH STRING/UNSTRING, AND ONE WITH MCS-10.  THE NEW  MODULES
     ARE AS FOLLOWS:


          DBDML

               A MODULE USED DURING PHASE C OF THE  SYNTAX  SCAN.
               THIS  MODULE  READS THE SCHEMA DEFINITION FILE AND
               MODIFIES THE SOURCE SCAN SO THAT THE DBMS-10  DATA
               DEFINITIONS ARE CORRECTLY SET UP.  THE ACTUAL WORK
               IS DONE BY THE ROUTINES  DMLVOK,  DMLVIO,  DMLERR,
               DMLIO.
                 ALSO STRLIB.REL (AND  STRING.UNV)  ARE  USED  BY
               THIS  MODULE.  STRLIB IS ACCESSED EXCLUSIVELY AS A
               .REL  FILE  AND  CAN  BE  REBUILT  ONLY  BY  USING
               STRLIB.CTL.   IF STRLIB.REL MUST BE CHANGED DURING
               THE PROCESS OF REBUILDING COBOL, STRLIB.CTL SHOULD
               BE RUN BEFORE COBOL.CTL IS SUBMITTED.


          DBGETF

               A DBMS-10 ROUTINE WHICH INITIALIZES THE PROCESSING
               OF  THE VARIOUS TEMPORARY FILES WHICH WERE CREATED
               BY "DML".


          STRGEN

               THE PHASE E ROUTINE WHICH GENERATES THE  CODE  FOR
COBOL V6A(332) DOCUMENTATION                              Page 25


               THE  STRING  AND  UNSTRING  VERBS.   BECAUSE  THIS
               MODULE IS ALSO USED HEAVILY TO  AID  IN  THE  CODE
               GENERATION PROCESS FOR THE "STRING" AND "UNSTRING"
               VERBS, IT IS SUPPLIED ON THE STANDARD RELEASE TAPE
               FOR ALL CUSTOMERS.


          MESGEN

               THE PHASE E ROUTINE WHICH GENERATES CODE  FOR  THE
               VARIOUS MCS-10 COMMUNICATIONS VERBS.
