4.0     INTERNAL CHANGES



          4.1     COBOLK HAS BEEN CHANGED SO THAT THE DATA  TABLE
                  (DATAB)  AND  THE CONSTANT-VALUE TABLE (VALTAB)
                  ARE PRINTED IN ENGLISH INSTEAD OF BINARY.  THIS
                  MODIFICATION SHOULD MAKE READING THE DATA TABLE
                  AND INTERPRETING DUMPS MUCH MORE MANAGEABLE.


          4.2     ALL SYNTAX TREES HAVE BEEN SEPARATED FROM THEIR
                  RESPECTIVE   PHASES   INTO   INDIVIDUAL  SOURCE
                  MODULES.  FOR EXAMPLE, THE OLD "COBOLC.MAC" HAS
                  BEEN    SEPARATED    INTO    "COBOLC.MAC"   AND
                  "CTREE.MAC".  EACH OF THESE SYNTAX TREES IS NOW
                  PLACED  INTO  "COBOLL.REL" SO THAT IT IS LOADED
                  WITH THE APPROPRIATE COMPILER PHASE.


          4.3     IN THE DEBUG VERSION OF THE COMPILER, THE TRACE
                  OF  THE  PHASE D SYNTAX TREE CAN BE SELECTIVELY
                  CONTROLLED BY THE "TRACE ON"  AND  "TRACE  OFF"
                  STATEMENTS.  IF THE "TP" SWITCH IS GIVEN AND NO
                  "TRACE OFF" APPEARS IN THE PROCEDURE  DIVISION,
                  THEN  THE ENTIRE PROCEDURE DIVISION SYNTAX SCAN
                  IS TRACED.


          4.4     FIVE NEW PARAMETER FILES (PURAB.MAC, PUREC.MAC,
                  PURED.MAC,   PUREE.MAC,  PURFG.MAC)  HAVE  BEEN
                  ADDED  TO  ELIMINATE  TERMINAL   INPUT   DURING
                  ASSEMBLY   OF  THE  PURE  AREAS.   THESE  FILES
                  CONTAIN ONLY ONE PARAMETER DEFINITION.


          4.5     ALL  COBOL  ASSEMBLY   PARAMETERS   HAVE   BEEN
                  COLLECTED  INTO  ONE  FILE CALLED "COBASM.MAC".
                  USERS SHOULD  INSERT  ALL  THEIR  FEATURE  TEST
                  SWITCH DEFINITIONS INTO THIS FILE.


          4.6     THE PROCESSING OF SCHEMA  FILES  IS  NO  LONGER
                  SEQUENTIAL.     DBMS    STYLE   PAGE   ORIENTED
                  PROCESSING IS NOW USED.
